			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Connections Show Podcast puts you ahead of the curve with the latest developments in Internet Technology.</p>
<p>The host, <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/StanRelihan" target="_new">Stan Relihan</a></strong>, is a leading <strong><a href="http://www.expertsearch.com.au/" target="_new">Recruiter, Headhunter</a></strong> &amp; <strong><a href="http://www.toplinked.com/top50.html" target="_new">Top 50 LinkedIn user</a></strong>, located in Sydney, Australia.</p>
<p>Each episode features guests from his extensive network &#8211; who share their experiences &amp; insights on how Online Networking and Web 2.0 tools &amp; resources can be used to create business advantage.</p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
<p><strong><a title="Using LinkedIn as a Business Tool" href="http://tinyurl.com/StanRelihan">Connections #000 &#8211; Using LinkedIn as a Business Tool</a></strong></p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/StanRelihan"><img title="Stan Relihan" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3279/2826872323_aaa544fedc.jpg" border="0" alt="Stan Relihan" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a></p>
<p>Although not strictly speaking an Episode of &#8220;The Connections Show&#8221;, it was this interview I did with Cameron Reilly (and the subsequent Challenge he set me) that kicked it all off to begin with.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested in learning about how to use LinkedIn as a Business Tool (or just plain curious &#8230; <a title="Using LinkedIn as Business Tool" href="http://tinyurl.com/StanRelihan"><strong>More</strong></a></p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
<p><strong><a title="Connections #001 - It all started with a Challenge ..." href="http://tinyurl.com/CameronReilly1">Connections #001 &#8211; It all started with a Challenge &#8230;</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/CameronReilly1"><img title="Cameron Reilly" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2125/2303712642_b5fcfe8778_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Cameron Reilly" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a></strong><strong> </strong></p>
<p>A few months ago, I was interviewed on Cameron Reilly&#8217;s &#8216;G&#8217;Day World&#8217; show, here on the Podcast Network, on the subject of &#8216;Using LinkedIn as a Business Tool&#8217;.</p>
<p>Many listeners found the show to be very helpful to them in communicating the benefits of LinkedIn to their friends &amp; colleagues &#8211; and it has since been picked up &#8230;<strong> <a href="http://tinyurl.com/CameronReilly1">More</a></strong></p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
<p><strong><a title="Connections #002 - Conversation with a LION" href="http://tinyurl.com/ChristianMayaud">Connections #002 &#8211; Conversation with a LION</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/ChristianMayaud"><img title="Christian Mayaud" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2125/2302877705_a9c78f013c_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Christian Mayaud" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a></strong></p>
<p>This week&#8217;s guest is Christian Mayaud &#8211; a successful Venture Capitalist whose amazing Rolodex formed part of the initial nucleus of LinkedIn users.</p>
<p>He&#8217;s also founder of the LinkedIn LIONs and one of LinkedIn&#8217;s most highly-connected users. In this interview, you can listen to Christian&#8217;s insights on the early days of LinkedIn &#8230; <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/ChristianMayaud">More</a></strong></p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
<p><strong><a title="Connections #003 - A Taste of LinkedIntelligence" href="http://tinyurl.com/ScottAllen">Connections #003 &#8211; A Taste of LinkedIntelligence</a></strong></p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/ScottAllen"><img title="Scott Allen" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3208/2303697868_1930071a3a_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Scott Allen" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a></p>
<p>This week&#8217;s guest is Scott Allen &#8211; Executive Editor, LinkedIn Series at &#8216;Happy About&#8217; and Co-author of &#8216;The Virtual Handshake: Opening Doors and Closing Deals Online&#8217;.</p>
<p>Scott is also a prominent Blogger, Corporate Speaker &amp; Trainer &#8211; and author of LinkedIntelligence.com &#8211; a very useful &amp; insightful web site on how to use LinkedIn effectively. &#8230; <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/ScottAllen">More</a></strong></p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
<p><strong><a title="Connections #004 - Talking with the Queen of Q &amp; A" href="http://tinyurl.com/SheilahEtheridge">Connections #004 &#8211; Talking with the Queen of Q &amp; A</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/SheilahEtheridge"><img title="Sheilah Etheridge" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2300/2380910011_f0ec86c5b9_m.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a></strong></p>
<p>My guest this week is Sheliah Etheridge &#8211; one of LinkedIn&#8217;s most active users. Regular users of LinkedIn will recognise Sheilah as the #1 &#8216;Answers Expert&#8217; on LinkedIn&#8217;s very popular Q &amp; A forum.</p>
<p>In this episode, Sheilah discusses her motivations and the rewards she receives from &#8230; <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/SheilahEtheridge">More</a></strong></p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3270/2889203278_786e30a369.jpg" alt="" vspace="5" width="640" height="1" /></p>
