			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/successinthecity" target="_new"><img title="Cynthia de Lorenzi" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2396/2221513503_7cb0da6675_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Cynthia de Lorenzi" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a> <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/successinthecity" target="_new"><strong>Cynthia de Lorenzi</strong></a> is a Public Speaker, <strong><a href="http://www.successinthecity.org/" target="_new">successful Entrepreneur</a></strong> and prolific Social Networker, originally from Texas, now based in Washington DC.</p>
<p>She&#8217;s also the wonderful Southern belle, that in <strong><a href="http://gdayworld.thepodcastnetwork.com/2007/03/28/gday-world-219-using-linkedin-as-a-business-tool/" target="_top">a unique sequence of events</a></strong>, catalyzed the birth of The Connections Show &#8211; following an introduction to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vint_Cerf" target="_new"><strong>Vint Cerf</strong></a>, a prominent figure (who is frequently referred to as &#8216;The Father of the Internet&#8217;) &#8211; and himself a <strong><a href="http://connections.thepodcastnetwork.com/2009/02/22/connections-050-history-of-the-internet-part-i/" target="_&quot;new&quot;">recent guest on The Connections Show</a></strong>.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Since Cynthia was indirectly responsible for the show&#8217;s inception, it&#8217;s only fitting that she and I got together for one last chat &#8211; to say &#8216;Good Bye&#8217; to the show and all the loyal listeners that have provided support and encouragement along the way.</p>
<p>Join us, in this, the final episode of The Connections Show, as Cynthia and I discuss some of the many developments that have occured over the last 18 months, as well as some of the new technologies and possibilities that lie ahead in Social Networking.</p>
