			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/iggypintado" target="_new"><img title="iggy Pintado" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2442/3538298734_fd9ca35796_o_d.png" border="0" alt="Iggy Pintado" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/iggypintado" target="_new">Iggy Pintado</a></strong> is an author, public speaker and online networking expert and trainer, based in Sydney, Australia.</p>
<p>In July, 2008, Iggy left the corporate environment to become an entrepreneur &#8211; and spent the following nine months researching and writing about his passion for online networking.</p>
<p>The result is &#8216;<strong><a href="http://www.connectiongeneration.com/" target="_new">Connection Generation&#8217;</a></strong> &#8211; a new book that highlights the fact that whether we realize it or not, everyone that has had access to a computer or mobile device since 1995 &#8211; regardless of age &#8211; is part of the Connection Generation.</p>
<p><br />
<a href="http://www.connectiongeneration.com/" target="_new"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2094/3538307480_4631b75ab0_o_d.png" border="0" alt="LinkedWorking" width="120" height="160" align="right" /></a>In this episode, Iggy discusses how connectedness is changing our world &#8211; and how connections between people, an further the exchange of information, experiences and ideas.</p>
<p>Whether you’re a business owner, corporate professional, entrepreneur, manager, student or teacher, this conversation provides new and refreshing insights on how to create business benefit from online and social networking.</p>
