			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.gartner.com/AnalystBiography?authorId=29763" target="_new"><img title="Andrew Walls" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3012/3101599467_5ced6c872a_o_d.png" border="0" alt="Andrew Walls" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a>Originally from the USA, but now located in Sydney, Australia, <a href="http://www.gartner.com/AnalystBiography?authorId=29763" target="_new"><strong>Andrew Walls</strong></a> is the Asia Pacific Director of Security &amp; Privacy at <strong><a href="http://www.gartner.com" target="_new">Gartner</a></strong>, the world&#8217;s leading IT Research &amp; Analysis Consultancy.</p>
<p>One of the themes that has emerged in conversations with some of my guests recently, is the subject of Security &amp; Personal Privacy on the Internet &#8211; specifically as it applies to Social Networking.</p>
<p>In this interview, Andrew discusses some of the many challenges facing IT Managers, CIO&#8217;s &amp; CTO&#8217;s in an environment that has been changed forever by the ubiquity &amp; permanence of digital data once it escapes into the &#8216;cloud.&#8217;</p>
<p></p>
<p>Whether you&#8217;re responsible for maintaining the systems of a large corporation, or a small start-up company &#8211; if you have Intellectual Property to protect, this podcast should be an essential part of your information universe.</p>
