			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://johnmccrea.myplaxo.com/" target="_new"><img title="John McCrea" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3280/3058613180_a3cdd22bf8_o_d.png" border="0" alt="John McCrea" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><strong><a href="http://johnmccrea.myplaxo.com/" target="_new">John McCrea</a></strong> is VP of Marketing at <strong><a href="http://www.plaxo.com" target="_new">Plaxo</a></strong>, in Mountain View, California.</p>
<p>He&#8217;s a seasoned veteran of the Internet &#8211; responsible for pioneering a number of online advances, including the first Internet advertising deal &amp; creation of the term &#8216;Powered By &#8230;&#8217;</p>
<p></p>
<p>In this interview, John discusses the role that Plaxo Pulse plays in connecting and updating people about their friends and business associates in the ever-changing Web 2.0 universe &#8211; as well as outlining some of the exciting changes and innovations on the horizon,  arising from the company&#8217;s recent acquisition by major media &amp; online services provider, <strong><a href="http://www.comcast.com/" target="_new">Comcast</a></strong>.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Web Links:</strong></span><br />
