			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/0/a3/373" target="_new"><img title="Mark Horstman" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3200/2780202893_dc6f8cf815.jpg" border="0" alt="Mark Horstman" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/0/a3/373" target="_new">Mark Horstman</a> </strong>is the host of <strong><a href="http://www.manager-tools.com" target="_new">Manager Tools</a></strong> &#8211; the world&#8217;s <strong><a href="http://www.digg.com/podcasts/view/business/" target="_new">#1 Business Podcast</a></strong></p>
<p>Mark and his business partner, <strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/0/201/b36" target="_new">Mike Auzenne</a></strong> have been providing valuable management techniques &amp; advice through their free weekly podcast since November 2005 &#8211; and have since achieved an enviable position as the most successful Business Podcast on the Internet.<br />
</p>
<p>In this engaging &amp; informative discussion, Mark talks about what motivated him to share his management expertise via the medium of Podcasting, how this has developed into a successful business &#8211; and most importantly, his thoughts and philosophy on Networking for Business.</p>
<p>This episode is essential listening for Managers, other Podcasters &amp; Bloggers &#8211; and anyone wishing to learn about more effective use of networking &amp; relationships.</p>
