			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/garyunger" target="_new"><img title="Gary Unger" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3278/2703550152_e5092693de.jpg" border="0" alt="Gary Unger" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/garyunger" target="_new">Gary Unger</a> </strong>is an Advertising, Design &amp; Marketing professional from Atlanta, Georgia in the USA. He&#8217;s also a first-time Author &#8211; of a book entitled: <strong><em><a href="http://tinyurl.com/62xfl8" target="_new">&#8220;How to be a Creative Genius (in five minutes or less)&#8221;</a></em></strong>.</p>
<p>What&#8217;s remarkable about Gary&#8217;s story is that he joined <strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com" target="_new">LinkedIn</a></strong> just over a month ago (on the advice of his Publisher) &#8211; with the express goal of using it to promote his book.</p>
<p>During this time, Gary has not only amassed over 600 connections &#8211; but more importantly, has been able to leverage this network to promote his book so effectively that it has already sold out at a number of locations, including <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/62xfl8" target="_new">Amazon</a></strong>, <a href="http://tinyurl.com/3g534d" target="_new"><strong>Borders</strong></a> and <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4swztt" target="_new">Barnes &amp; Noble</a></strong>!</p>
<p></p>
<p>In this Episode, Gary shares the simple, no-nonsense methods he&#8217;s employed to achieve this outstanding result &#8211; as well as some of the overwhelming &amp; exciting experiences that have happened to him along this journey of discovery.</p>
