			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/ronbatesprofile" target="_new"><img title="Ron Bates" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2117/2388068959_9082618a80_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Ron Bates" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/ronbatesprofile" target="_top">Ron Bates</a></strong> is a Headhunter, Executive Search Consultant &amp; Recruiter based in San Francisco, USA.</p>
<p>Heâ€™s also widely known as LinkedIn&#8217;s most-connected user &#8211; with around 40,000 direct Connections. However, while Ron&#8217;s name is well-known to many people, he himself maintains a fairly low personal profile.</p>
<p></p>
<p>In this interview, we chat with LinkedIn&#8217;s &#8216;Man of Mystery&#8217;, as Ron reveals many details about himself, how he first became involved with <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/" target="_top"><strong>LinkedIn</strong></a>, the time he spends each week maintaining and interacting with his network &#8211; and the business benefit he receives from having such a large number of connections.</p>
<p>For anyone that is curious about what being a <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/" target="_top"><strong>LinkedIn</strong></a> &#8216;Power User&#8217; is all about &#8211; this is is definitely the place to find out.</p>
