		<title>Connections #026 &#8211; Insights from a $3 Billion Man</title>
		<link>http://connections.thepodcastnetwork.com/2008/03/17/connections-026-insights-from-a-3-billion-man/</link>
		<comments>http://connections.thepodcastnetwork.com/2008/03/17/connections-026-insights-from-a-3-billion-man/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2008 08:01:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Stan Relihan</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Business]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[General]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Networking]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Podcast]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Web 2.0]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://connections.thepodcastnetwork.com/2008/03/17/connections-026-insights-from-a-3-billion-man/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[David Moore is Director of Enterprise Engagements at Hewlett Packard in Sydney, Australia &#8211; and through the course of his career, has been involved in closing deals totaling in excess of $3 Billion. Prior to joining HP, David had a long career at Deloitte Consulting, as Industry Leader in Energy, Telecommunications &#38; Government, followed by [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img title="David Moore" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3130/2340155122_cea6b97c03_m.jpg" border="0" alt="David Moore" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" />David Moore is Director of Enterprise Engagements at <strong><a href="http://www.hp.com" target="_new">Hewlett Packard</a></strong> in Sydney, Australia &#8211; and through the course of his career, has been involved in closing deals totaling in excess of $3 Billion.</p>
<p>Prior to joining HP, David had a long career at <strong><a href="http://www.deloitte.com" target="_new">Deloitte Consulting</a></strong>, as Industry Leader in Energy, Telecommunications &amp; Government, followed by responsibility for Systems Integration, Outsourcing &amp; Consulting in Asia Pacific, Japan and South Africa.</p>
<p>This background prepared him well for his current role, leading HP&#8217;s large, complex service engagements for the top Corporate Enterprises and Government Agencies &#8211; with an average deal size of $200 &#8211; 500 Million.</p>
<p></p>
<p>In this episode, David shares a few of insights he&#8217;s gained through working on deals of this magnitude, together with some predictions on the impact of the Internet on the Enterprise.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.feedburner.com/fb/a/emailverifySubmit?feedId=1560722" target="_new"><img title="Subscribe via E-mail" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3068/2918643244_1edc7777a2_o_d.png" border="0" alt="Subscribe via E-mail" vspace="0" width="143" height="26" /></a> <a href="itpc://connections.thepodcastnetwork.com/feed/" target="_new"><img title="Subscribe via iTunes" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3098/2918643246_e5c1d11959_o_d.png" border="0" alt="Subscribe via iTunes" vspace="0" width="143" height="26" /></a><br />
