			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/jeffsheard" target="_new"><img title="Jeff Sheard" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2114/2369504583_fedf99d424.jpg" border="0" alt="Jeff Sheard" hspace="5" width="90" height="90" align="left" /></a><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/jeffsheard" target="_new"><strong>Jeff Sheard</strong></a> is the Channels Director for <strong><a href="http://www.cisco.com/" target="_new">Cisco Systems</a></strong> in Sydney, Australia.</p>
<p>In this Episode, Jeff discusses how <strong><a href="http://www.cisco.com" target="_new">Cisco</a></strong> is using new <strong><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_2.0" target="_new">Web 2.0</a></strong> applications &amp; other tools, such as <strong><a href="http://www.facebook.com/" target="_new">Facebook</a></strong>, <strong><a href="http://secondlife.com/whatis/" target="_new">Second Life</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://www.cisco.com/en/US/netsol/ns669/networking_solutions_solution_segment_home.html" target="_new">Immersive Telepresence</a></strong> as tools for <strong><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_collaboration" target="_new">Online Collaboration</a></strong> &#8211; and the productivity benefits &amp; cost savings they deliver.</p>
<p>This includes saving $200 Million p.a. in travel expenditure &#8211; not to mention the reduction in <strong><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_footprint" target="_new">Corporate Carbon Footprint</a></strong>.</p>
